sql:
SELECT 
    SUM(loan_amount * interest_rate / 100) AS total_interest_earned
FROM loans;

SELECT SUM(repayment_amount) AS total_repayment
FROM repayments
WHERE loan_id = 1;

SELECT name
FROM loan_officers
WHERE experience > 5;

external_knowledge:
Active loans refer to loans that are currently being repaid and have not been fully repaid or defaulted on yet;

The average annual income of borrowers provides insight into the financial stability of the borrowers the loan officers are working with;

A threshold of at least 10 active loans is used to focus on loan officers with a significant portfolio of active loans, indicating their level of activity and responsibility.

